ts =E2=80=9Cdo not receive or retain the full state of the blockchain.=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0
In this architecture, Celo can get scalability, since the full nodes and va=
lidators can run expensive hardware, alongside decentralization, because th=
e system incentivizes a ton of full nodes to run on the network and serve l=
ight clients. Already, there are about 1,000 full nodes on Celo compared to=
 6,000 on Ethereum =E2=80=93 not there yet, but decentralized relative to t=
he volume of activity.=C2=A0
