e;">zK-SNARK-based</a></strong> light client protocol, making Celo&#8217;s =
light client <strong>1.7 million times lighter than Ethereum&#8217;s</stron=
g>. cLabs, the company Marek helps to run, will run the first server to gen=
erate proofs daily, but <strong>anyone is able to generate proofs</strong>.=
 One amazing feature of Plumo is that these SNARK proofs can be verified in=
 a WASM-based library that can run in a web application, enabling dapps tha=
t are "Capital D" Dapps &#8211; ie truly Decentralized and not connected th=
rough a trusted RPC server.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">As one last point on decentralizati=
on, <strong>Celo or cLabs has never run a validator &#8211; </strong>they&#=
8217;ve been run by major Celo holders and independents since Day 1. This i=
s in contrast to many other proof of stake L1s where core teams or foundati=
ons have stood up the network, and some of which still run large portions o=
f the network.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Celo's PoS consensus and light client isn'=
t the only innovative technology that the team built ahead of launch. Inspi=
red by Tezos's on-chain governance, the team worked to launch Celo with <st=
rong>full on-chain governance right from the start</strong>, allowing the C=
elo community to fine tune protocol parameters and even upgrade core protoc=
ol pieces. There have already been <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.co=
m/c/eJxFUMuOhCAQ_JrhaABB8cBhL_MbpIXWIaNgoN2Nf7_seNikU32oVOrhgXDN5bJHrsT-wNF=
