s and composability mean that you can build <strong>smart contracts to comp=
ute anything</strong>, and then chain them together to build increasingly c=
omplex things, more quickly.&#8221;&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Decentralized finance=
 (or DeFi) generates novel use cases for and from programmable and composab=
le money around permissionless lending, insurance, options, and more.&nbsp;=
</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 1em 0;">But if we&#8217;re combining the programmability of arbitrary =
computer programs with money&#8217;s use cases as store of value, medium of=
 exchange, and unit of account with computers&#8217; ability to store, calc=
ulate, and translate large amounts of data, it feels like <strong>we&#8217;=
re very early in a new monetary paradigm</strong> that will have wild and u=
nimaginable consequences, like the original advent of paper money or debt o=
r computer programs did.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Celo seems like the L1 that&#821=
